Infographic: India’s among world’s worst places for children under-5 years 
7-3-2017 
India’s among world’s worst places for children under-5 years

Unsafe water, lack of sanitation, inadequate hygiene and air pollution but indoor and outdoor is responsible for India being among the worst places in the world for children under 5 years of age due to environmental risks. Globally, more than 1 in 4 deaths of children under 5 years of age are attributable to unhealthy environments and India has the second highest death rate among young children due to environmental risks. Clearly, India needs improved sanitation to save children 
